snippet.title: The Witcher 4 — Unreal Engine 5 Tech Demo
snippet.description: CD PROJEKT RED and Epic Games come together at the State of Unreal to show an early development Unreal Engine 5 tech demo for The Witcher 4 — showcasing some of the innovative technology and features that will help bring the game’s open world to life. Keep in mind this isn’t gameplay of The Witcher 4 itself, but a deep dive into the technological foundation of the new Witcher saga.

What is Roblox? ROBLOX is an online virtual playground and workshop, where kids of all ages can safely interact, create, have fun, and learn. It’s unique in that practically everything on ROBLOX is designed and constructed by members of the community. ROBLOX is designed for 13 to 18 year olds, but it is open to people of all ages. Each player starts by choosing an avatar and giving it an identity. They can then explore ROBLOX — interacting with others by chatting, playing games, or collaborating on creative projects. Each player is also given their own piece of undeveloped real estate along with a virtual toolbox with which to design and build anything — be it a navigable skyscraper, a working helicopter, a giant pinball machine, a multiplayer “Capture the Flag” game or some other, yet-to-be-dreamed-up creation. There is no cost for this first plot of virtual land. By participating and by building cool stuff, ROBLOX members can earn specialty badges as well as ROBLOX dollars (“Robux”). In turn, they can shop the online catalog to purchase avatar clothing and accessories as well as premium building materials, interactive components, and working mechanisms.

#Roblox #foltyn

snippet.title: 6-3-2025 Sunny Gets Around!
snippet.description:
For anyone who didn’t hear, Sunny fledged (flew from the nest for the first time) yesterday morning at 10:46! 

She circled a bit to head toward Jackie and Shadow’s favorite roost tree and landed near the top of it—it’s possible that after seeing her parents head to that tree so often, Sunny decided it looked like a safe place to go for her first flight. Our camera operators were able to find her so we knew where she was and that she was safe.

After spending the night where she landed yesterday, this morning Sunny spread her wings again.

While Jackie and Shadow spent the night on their usual favorite roosting limbs in that tree, Sunny was on the branches above them—and yes, they were aware she was there, as they looked up at her a few times. 

This morning while we panned Cam2, the wide-angle camera, to check on them…Sunny chose that moment to fly back to the nest tree…

…the cams are set to move slowly so as not to disturb the eagles or any other wildlife, so we missed her flight…but, watching from the nest, Gizmo tracked Sunny’s trip. 

Sunny apparently couldn’t quite figure out the front or back door entrances to the nest itself and instead, landed on top of the nest tree canopy! 
She stayed up above the nest, moving about to different areas for over an hour and a half. While Sunny bounced around up there, Gizmo stared up often, trying to figure out what Sunny was doing.

Then Sunny flew off the nest tree canopy and over to the nearby Simba Tree…she’s been there for over an hour. She seems to be checking out all the nearby trees to get a handle on this traveling around wherever you want idea.

As she can now go anywhere, we will work to keep an eye/or a lens on her when we can as she continues her new explorations! And we will continue watching Gizmo as she keeps a curious eye on Sunny’s movements and does her own development to decide when she's ready to fly.

Sandy

snippet.title: JAMAL ROBERTS GETS RAW ABOUT ABANDONMENT, FAITH, AND AMERICAN IDOL SUCCESS
snippet.description:
American Idol winner Jamal Roberts joins The Love You Moore Show and opens up like never before. From childhood abandonment and losing his stepmom during COVID, to raising three daughters and balancing his faith with fame, this interview is a powerful testimony about purpose, healing, and what it really means to be chosen.

Join Our Patreon: https://www.patreon.com/WillieMooreJrLive

You’ll hear:
 • His reaction to winning American Idol
 • How church hurt and Sunday Best almost broke him
 • The moment that almost made a grieving mom take her life—and how Jamal’s song stopped her
 • What he prays for in a partner
 • His heart for real estate and generational change
 • Why he’s not just a gospel artist—he’s a soul singer with a mission

🎤 “It was never about the stage… it was about healing.”
🙌 Get ready to cry, laugh, and walk away with faith renewed.

This episode is filled with encouragement through difficult times and a reminder that your gift can make room for you, no matter the obstacles. Jamal’s journey is proof that faith and perseverance can lead to extraordinary breakthroughs.

If you’ve ever faced setbacks or wondered about the purpose of your journey, this episode will deeply resonate with you. Don’t miss this uplifting conversation packed with wisdom, heart, and inspiration!

🎥 Subscribe to the channel for more inspirational stories and exclusive content.  

Your miracle is in your hands, let this story inspire you to believe again.

snippet.title: 6-2-2025 SUNNY DID IT!
snippet.description:
At 10:46 am this morning, Sunny flew from the upper Y-branch right out into the world! 

She put up her wings to catch the wind and then jumped up and let those beautiful wings carry her. She circled back around toward Shadow and Jackie’s favorite roost tree…

Gizmo watched the whole thing from right beside Sunny. She looked completely fascinated and kept her eyes on Sunny flying away from the nest.
…and a bit later, our awesome camera operatiors were able to find Sunny, perching near the top of the roost tree (upper center on the screen) – watch closely and her practice flapping will show you where she is. 

Sunny may return to the nest…Jackie and Shadow’s previous eaglets have all done that. It is all up to her at this point. But in any case, Jackie and Shadow will be keeping an eye on Sunny, bringing her food, guarding her and teaching her all that she needs to know to be out in the world. All while they also continue taking care of Gizmo. Gizmo probably now has a lot to think about.
Congratulations, Sunny! – as we get to feel exuberance of this beautiful success and at the same time, sadness for change that means seeing her less often. Sunny is out in the world!

Sandy

snippet.title: Dear Joe Rogan, I'm an Archaeologist and the Helicopter Hieroglyphs aren't Real
snippet.description:
Joe Rogan recently had Zahi Hawass on his podcast. In a clip of another episode where he was recounting that interview, the famous Helicopter Hieroglyphs at Abydos were brought up, along with the 'wooden plane' which I assume is the Saqqara Bird. (Graham Hancock was also mentioned but let's not get into that). 

Link to the original video: https://youtu.be/niEA63aUarI?si=Ha2E14NJ95whMwGi

What to watch next if you're interested in ancient Egypt: 
https://youtu.be/wT7xmcWUcaw
https://youtu.be/XdeKXWXbC0Y
How the Pyramids Were Built - LATEST EVIDENCE https://youtu.be/9DUuLemfa-4
Who REALLY Built the Pyramids? https://youtu.be/bdtFb-xIAmg

📚 Buy my book 'The Other Ancient Civilisations' 📚
US/International: https://amzn.to/3Y38BFa
UK: https://amzn.to/3BGcoki

👉🏼 Get early access and help support the channel here: https://www.patreon.com/digitwithraven

✅ Let's connect! 
INSTAGRAM: https://www.instagram.com/digitwithra...

These hieroglyphs are not evidence of advanced ancient technology or aliens, they are in fact, an early case of white out, otherwise known as a palimpsest when referring to similar act in a manuscript where text has been scraped or washed off in preparation for new text to be written overtop. This relief isn’t one original set of carvings, it’s actually two overlapping inscriptions of the official kingly titles of Ramesses II and Seti I. When Ramesses II was renovating the Temple of Seti I, he has someone cover up Seti I’s royal titulary and replace it with his own. Then, over time, as some of the plaster eroded and fell away, creating a weird combo of signs that now look like these modern vehicles.

RESOURCES
Baumann, Stefan (2018). "Ägypten, das Land der Mysterien und pseudowissenschaftlicher Mystifizierungen". In: Stefan Baumann (ed.), Fakten und Fiktionen. Archäologie vs. Pseudowissenschaft, Zaberns Bildbände zur Archäologie, Darmstadt, 89.

Roberson, Joshua Aaron (2016). "Anatomy of a Palimpsest: The Not-so-Strange Case of the 'Abydos Helicopter'". Kmt. 27: 61–66.

AERODYNAMIC INVESTIGATION ON THE ARTEFACT “BIRD OF SAQQARA” https://wm.pb.edu.pl/actamechanica/wp-content/uploads/sites/18/2023/07/46_2022_111_ZIEROW_LESEMANN_AMA-D-22-00096.pdf

snippet.title: E-40: Tiny Desk Concert
snippet.description:
This Black Music Month, Tiny Desk honors the anniversaries of landmark albums that have shaped the course of music and culture.

Bobby Carter | June 2, 2025
Bay Area ambassador E-40 moves with the energy of an up-and-coming emcee, but he's been around a minute. To put it 40 Water's way: "I've been doing this since Kermit the Frog was a pollywog!" Our biggest hurdle to clear was packing in three decades of music at the Tiny Desk, but 40 Fonzarelli and his band clocked weeks of rehearsal to make sure this office was rockin'.

E-40's sophomore solo album In a Major Way dropped in 1995, one of the most competitive years in hip-hop history, with certified classics dropping weekly by the likes of 2Pac, Mobb Deep, Goodie Mob, Bone Thugs-n-Harmony, Ol' Dirty Bastard, Raekwon and GZA. Straightforward and plain has never been E-40's nature, and that left-of-center spit has been the thing that has sustained his illustrious entertainment career.

At the Desk, Charlie Hustle sets things off with "Da Bumble" from In a Major Way and continues to bounce through a catalog of big hits sprinkled with nods to his day ones. Producer Lil Jon brought him back to the mainstream in the early 2000s with "Tell Me When to Go," "U and Dat" and "Snap Yo Fingers," while TikTok injected new life in "Choices (Yup)" and introduced him to Gen Z. "I'm on my fourth wind!" 40 tells us. No lies told.

SET LIST
"Da Bumble"
"Yay Area" 
"Sprinkle Me"
"Captain Save a Hoe"
"Snap Yo Fingers"
"U and Dat" 
"Choices (Yup)"

"1-Luv" 
"Function"
"Tell Me When to Go"

Marcus Phillips: bass, keys

snippet.title: 3 Minecraft Speedrunners VS Herobrine
snippet.description:
We coded Herobrine into Minecraft, can we survive him, and beat Minecraft?

Patreon (Plugin): https://www.patreon.com/DreamWasTaken

Follow my socials:
➽ Twitter - @dream
➽ Instagram - @dreamwastaken
➽ Snapchat - @dreampublic

Merch: https://www.dream.shop

GeorgeNotFound: @GeorgeNotFound 
Sapnap: @Sapnap 

We decided to take on Herobrine in Minecraft Manhunt! This video is a different rendition of normal Manhunt, where we go up against an AI bot that has abilities like the legend of Herobrine!

Herobrine has and probably always will be Minecraft's greatest evil villain. If Steve is Minecraft's best friend, Herobrine is it's enemy.

This was super challenging, but was a lot of fun. We made a video a while ago where we took on a terminator, and this is similar to that, but even more advanced and with special abilities!

Baritone: https://github.com/cabaletta/baritone

This is a new Minecraft but, 1.16 challenge that we have decided to try. I try to beat the game, while my friend AND my friend AND my friend tries to prevent me from doing it. It's a race, and it's super intense and we had a lot of laughs. I love doing these challenges.

If this video gets 1,000,000 likes we'll do a rematch!

Not Minecraft, But Water Rises or Minecraft, But Lava Rises, or any other but challenge like that. This is a speed run / speed runner of Minecraft against a killer / assassin

#MinecraftManhunt

snippet.title: Elden Ring Nightreign - YOU'RE PLAYING IT WRONG!
snippet.description:
Elden Ring Nightreign - YOU'RE PLAYING IT WRONG!
In this Elden Ring Nightreign video, we're going to be talking about how you're probably playing Nightreign wrong. There are a lot of new players out there who are making a lot of mistakes that most of us have made. When we first started learning this game, they may have been having a rough time with it, but there is a point where this game clicks for you when you get far enough into the game, and this is one of the reasons that we gave it such a review score on the channel once this game really clicked. That's when the fun starts happening in this game, and you have to play enough to really get to that point and really understand some of the mechanics of that. So in this video, we're going to go through some things that will further help you get through your playthrough. Kind of illustrates some things that might show you how you're doing things incorrectly.
